WEBVTT

00:06.367 --> 00:08.632
Uh-oh, she's
got that bounce.

00:08.842 --> 00:10.311
Do I need to call HR?

00:10.399 --> 00:13.707
No, I mean the bounce of a cop
who just put away a bad guy.

00:13.795 --> 00:15.709
After a hell of a long day
in court.

00:15.813 --> 00:17.639
Detectives?
Got a lady here

00:17.727 --> 00:19.233
saying she needs
to report a murder.

00:20.865 --> 00:22.694
All right. Thanks, Meyers.

00:26.709 --> 00:28.043
Detective Reagan,

00:28.130 --> 00:29.850
my partner Detective Baez.

00:29.938 --> 00:30.983
And you are?

00:31.071 --> 00:32.377
Uh, Roxy Smith.

00:32.561 --> 00:34.217
So who got murdered,
Ms. Smith?

00:34.440 --> 00:35.819
I don't know.

00:35.907 --> 00:37.256
I-I mean, they
haven't been yet,

00:37.344 --> 00:38.686
I don't think.

00:39.092 --> 00:40.530
Sorry, all this
has me creeped out.

00:40.618 --> 00:42.381
And us confused.

00:43.608 --> 00:46.717
I tend bar at a place
on Avenue B, The Clasp.

00:46.909 --> 00:48.616
Last night,
I overheard

00:48.704 --> 00:50.619
one of our regulars, Joe,

00:50.707 --> 00:52.827
saying he'd pay
to have someone killed.

00:53.027 --> 00:54.202
Like, serious money.

00:54.305 --> 00:55.678
I'm familiar
with The Clasp.

00:55.765 --> 00:58.817
It's half barflies, half
college students, all drunk.

00:58.905 --> 01:01.678
Including all of the bartenders.

01:02.147 --> 01:03.420
Okay.

01:03.756 --> 01:05.286
I had a couple shots.

01:05.373 --> 01:06.582
Mm. And if we know anything,

01:06.670 --> 01:08.735
it's that drunk people say
drunk things.

01:08.852 --> 01:10.490
But this Joe guy's
sick in the head.

01:10.592 --> 01:11.975
And a crap tipper.

01:12.264 --> 01:13.668
Not that that matters.

01:13.756 --> 01:15.629
Apparently, it does. Look,

01:15.717 --> 01:18.147
people who hurt other people
should be stopped.

01:19.569 --> 01:21.090
Sit tight.

01:23.506 --> 01:25.664
I don't know.
This whole thing seems thin.

01:25.759 --> 01:27.538
Yea...

01:27.842 --> 01:30.497
You know, the second collar
I ever had in my career

01:30.585 --> 01:32.848
was a guy
named Frank Blake.

01:33.350 --> 01:34.850
Did security
at The Clasp.

01:34.938 --> 01:36.358
He, uh, threw out
some kids.

01:36.446 --> 01:38.274
One of them mouthed off.

01:38.624 --> 01:39.768
He snapped.

01:39.855 --> 01:41.683
Jammed a pool cue
into the kid's eye.

01:41.770 --> 01:43.319
Killed him on the spot.

01:45.514 --> 01:47.306
So, what does
that mean?

01:47.774 --> 01:50.330
Means I'm gonna
have to, uh...

01:50.869 --> 01:52.689
make another appearance.

01:59.157 --> 02:00.333
You know,

02:00.421 --> 02:02.080
it's called "quitting time"
for a reason.

02:02.168 --> 02:04.299
Great. Thanks.
I'll see you tomorrow.

02:04.433 --> 02:06.681
Come on. Four nights in a row?

02:07.167 --> 02:09.142
Even the bad guys
sleep sometimes.

02:09.245 --> 02:12.190
And yet cases still don't
magically get themselves ready

02:12.278 --> 02:13.454
for court.

02:13.541 --> 02:15.135
Anything I
can help with?

02:16.021 --> 02:17.299
Yeah.

02:17.545 --> 02:20.199
Explain to me again
why we hired Alice Dornan

02:20.286 --> 02:21.752
as our psychiatric consultant.

02:21.840 --> 02:23.080
'Cause she's a
top-notch shrink.

02:23.168 --> 02:24.197
Who's now saying

02:24.285 --> 02:25.500
that Martina Volo,
the nanny

02:25.588 --> 02:27.197
that abused
that little girl,

02:27.293 --> 02:29.328
is not competent to stand trial.

02:29.416 --> 02:30.548
Well, maybe she's right.

02:30.726 --> 02:32.945
Or maybe she's the one
who's out of her mind.

02:33.033 --> 02:35.209
Why? Because you don't like
her diagnosis?

02:35.334 --> 02:37.989
Martina Volo
is competent and guilty...

02:38.077 --> 02:40.039
No ifs, ands or buts about it.

02:40.127 --> 02:43.101
Look, I'm the last guy
to defend an insanity plea,

02:43.189 --> 02:46.226
but Dornan's got scads
of forensic experience

02:46.314 --> 02:49.929
and knows a lot more about
this stuff than me or you.

02:50.017 --> 02:53.134
Fine. Then call her and tell her
to be here tomorrow

02:53.222 --> 02:54.789
at 10:00 a.m. sharp.

02:55.295 --> 02:56.796
Erin, it's late.
She's not in.

02:56.884 --> 02:58.101
Then leave a message.

02:58.189 --> 03:00.761
Because I want to hear
this expert opinion of hers

03:00.849 --> 03:02.203
in person.

